docs.summary:
This endpoint will be called by the Wix Shipping Service to registered Shipping/Delivery Providers for the matched Shipping Rule based on the requested destination of the items being sent. For example, a Local Delivery provider might be associated to a number of shipping rule.

Input:

Headers: instance_id, locale Body: 1. Location Information - list of origins and the destination of the items to be shipped 2. Items - a list of items with full details such as: name, sku, full catalog id, quantity, price details, request Will call with list of origins from which requested items could be shipped, and the list of items 3. Pricing Options - options for how the price of shipping rates should be returned, such as currency

Output:

List of Rate Options which match the rate request, each with the following fields: 1. Service - code and details of the service for this shipping option; 2. Delivery Logistics - logistics of how to make the delivery, such as instructions, pickup location (relevant for pickup/lockers), and delivery time guarantee 3. Cost of the rates option, with optional extras such as insurance, packaging etc.

Should we also add contact details of the addressee such as name, email and phone in the case that rate might be dependent on the

enum - grams, klogram, ounze, pounds,.... -
note that in a single store will have all products with same weight unit, but if a non-stores user calls this service,
they might want to define unit per item

other costs such as insurance, handling & packaging for fragile items etc.

members.doc: Set of key-value pairs. custom values, including things such as shipping_product_group_id etc....

members.doc: weight of each item - since this service might be called by multiple other verticals, we will pass weight with unit for each item

members.doc: name and sku are redundant if using item id. Though maybe redundancy is not a bad thing for SPIs

members.name: quantity
members.doc: the amount of items for that specific product

members.name: sku
members.doc: unique sku for item - this is useful if shipping provider has copy of Wix catalog and can suggest rate options based on these sku's

members.name: isShippable
members.doc:
whether the item is shippable. We provide non-shippable items since the provider might take inclusive of non-shippable items
 into account when calculating shipping

members.name: price
members.doc: Price of all items after discount (multiplied by quantity)

members.name: itemIdentifier
members.doc: fully qualified identifier of the item

 relevant catalogues to get the origins of the items, so that can call connected providers with full input
